items.fromString:
Provide the ability to create / edit a view by specifying the node / edge types.
Also allow the user to filter on specific attributes.
The slippery slope to a query language.
items.toString:
Provide the ability to create / edit a view by specifying the node / edge types.
Also allow the user to filter on specific attributes.
The slippery slope to a query language.

There needs to be a UI element to define specific filters on the nodes and links. This allows users to filter down the data set by attribute values. A field to define a query language markup could suffice to do this.

With dynamic filters applied on node & link attributes there should be the ability to edit and remove these filters to update the graph

* Pair
* Create a Jenkins job to run tests build app with webpack and deploy with convox

To manage the deployment, versioning, scaling and logging of our docker apps we want to use Convox on the rig to manage our apps.

* Provision a Convox stack on the new rig through ansible by running 'convox install' - ensure they have different IP ranges though

* Create a Jenkins job to run tests build app with webpack and deploy with convox
